xv6 is a re-implementation of Dennis Ritchie's and Ken Thompson's Unix
Version 6 (v6).  xv6 loosely follows the structure and style of v6,
but is implemented for a modern RISC-V multiprocessor using ANSI C.

_______________________________________________________________________

CUSTOM MEMORY ALLOCATOR EXTENSION

This repository contains a modified version of the xv6 operating system
extended with a custom kernel memory allocator.

The project implements a slab allocator backed by a buddy allocator to
support efficient object allocation and memory block management within
the xv6 kernel.

KEY FEATURES

- Slab allocator for small-object caching
- Buddy allocator for physical memory block management
- Thread-safe allocation mechanisms
- Integration with xv6 kernel subsystems
- Custom system calls exposing allocator functionality

FILES ADDED

The following files were added as part of the custom memory allocator implementation:

- `kernel/slab.c` - implementation of the slab allocator
- `kernel/slab.h` - slab allocator interface and data structures
- `kernel/buddy.c` - buddy allocator implementation
- `kernel/buddy.h` - buddy allocator data structures and API
- `user/main.c` - tests

